<div class="definition" id="definition-OV" acro="OV" titletext="Orthogonal Vectors">
<h5 class="definition">
<span class="type">Definition </span><span class="acro">OV</span> <span class="titletext"> Orthogonal Vectors</span>
</h5>
<p>A pair of vectors, $\vect{u}$ and $\vect{v}$, from $\complex{m}$ are <em class="term">orthogonal</em> if their inner product is zero, that is, $\innerproduct{\vect{u}}{\vect{v}}=0$.</p>
